ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/image-11.png
CATEGORIES:Talks,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260706T050507Z
DESCRIPTION:Isamu Noguchi in India\, c. 1970s. The Noguchi Museum Archives\, 08014. © The Isamu Noguchi Foundation and Garden Museum\, New York / Artists Rights Society (ARS)\, New York.\nIsamu Noguchi wrote in 1949 that the site of Mahabalipuram was his “first and most authentic lesson.” Between then and his death in 1988\, Noguchi visited India at least eleven times. Yet there has been little investigation into the nature of this long and deep connection\, and the impact it had on the sculptor’s artistic philosophy and practice.\n\nThis talk by Kalyani Madhura Ramachandran sheds light on the sculptor’s enduring interest in the art of early India\, including Sanchi\, Elephanta\, and Mahabalipuram\, among numerous other ancient sites\, and traces the centrality of the “matter of sculpture” in his approach. In looking at and alongside Noguchi\, this talk expands our current understanding of the sculptor’s work and calls for material approaches to the study of sculpture from early India.\n\nThis programme at MAP is part of A Closer Look\, a monthly series of research-focused talks by artists\, curators and art historians focusing on visual cultures of South Asia.
DTEND:20260718T120000Z
DTSTART:20260718T103000Z
SUMMARY:Isamu Noguchi and the Stone Sculpture of Early India
UID:1322@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/isamu-noguchi-and-the-stone-sculpture-of-early-india/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Website-cover-images-new-32.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260702T063109Z
DESCRIPTION:Inspired by Living Botanicals\, this hands-on workshop invites participants to slow down and observe the colours\, textures and changing forms of plants before translating these observations into crochet. Beginning with a guided exploration of the exhibition\, participants will learn beginner-friendly crochet techniques to create cascading wisteria blossoms and intertwining vines.\n\nThrough the slow\, repetitive act of stitching\, the workshop explores ideas of growth\, seasonality and transformation. Individual creations will come together as a collaborative installation\, reflecting the exhibition's themes while celebrating collective making\, close observation and the many ways craft can deepen our engagement with the natural world.
DTEND:20260711T080000Z
DTSTART:20260711T060000Z
SUMMARY:Crocheting The Living Botanicals
UID:1329@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/22443/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Website-cover-images-new-2026-01-27T094537.573.png
CATEGORIES:Reading Circle,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260703T070654Z
DESCRIPTION:From enchanted lands\, curses\, and boons to the realities of the modern climate crisis\, this reading circle invites participants to reflect on our evolving relationship with the natural worl. We invite you to explore stories and ideas that provoke\, challenge\, and inspire uncovering ways of understanding environmental change while drawing on collective wisdom\, resistance\, and imagination to learn how to listen to the planet again.\n\nDrawing from the themes explored in Beneath the Turning Sky the sessions engage with ecology and climate through a range of texts spanning folklore\, ecofeminism\, Indigenous knowledge systems\, environmental history\, and climate critique.\n\nUpon registration\, participants will be sent text extracts that will be discussed during the session. \n\nThis event is in conjunction with our ongoing permanent exhibition Beneath the Turning Sky. 
DTEND:20260718T110000Z
DTSTART:20260718T093000Z
SUMMARY:BTS Reading Circle
UID:1330@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/bts-reading-circle/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Website-cover-images-new-94.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260703T033201Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a guided exploration of both the exhibition and the Beneath The Turning Sky Library\, where you'll discover a diverse selection of texts ranging from comics and graphic narratives to fiction\, poetry\, and critical theory. Together\, we'll reflect on how reading can open new ways of engaging with the exhibition and its themes.\n\nThe session concludes with a shared reading and browsing experience\, offering participants special access to the library. Explore the collection at your own pace\, share your favourite excerpts\, recommend books you'd like to see included\, and contribute to the evolving vision of the Beneath The Turning Sky Library as a space for collective learning and exchange.
DTEND:20260707T113000Z
DTSTART:20260707T083000Z
SUMMARY:Library Open Day
UID:1328@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/library-open-day/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/HP-Slider-Images-Desktop-1.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260629T071312Z
DESCRIPTION:We need\, in every community\, a group of angelic troublemakers - Bayard Rustin\n\nThe joy of being unapologetically authentic is a gift that we\, the queer-transgender community\, can share with the world. In this 3 hour offering\, we will use arts to channel our resistance by celebrating who we are. We will dance\, draw and craft words to resist efforts that seek to invisibilise us. The world should know that no matter what\, we will still party! \n\nLet our joy and celebration be their trouble. \n\nThis event is presented in conjunction with the exhibition warrior garments\, on view at MAP until August 2\, 2026.\n\nThis programme is part of LGBTQIA+ programming and is an attempt to amplify narratives from within the queer community through film\, dialogue\, and collective reflection.
DTEND:20260712T113000Z
DTSTART:20260712T083000Z
SUMMARY:The Party Don’t Stop!
UID:1325@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/the-party-dont-stop/
END:VEVENT
